column5: Jen did those Bald Eagle Pics show up ...ok now show your big cat ..

Nope, as by the time I got my camera turned on and ready the bald eagle had landed in its nest... so all I got was a picture of a nest a tree and the idea that something is in it.  Was truly amazing though without a doubt.     Here is the bigger catfish that I brought in...     Thanks again fishmaster, next time Easton and I will join you.
Nice chanell cat jen....way to go...cheers

The evening began with a fire in my oven... now that was a great joy seeing as I was cooking for the weekend and really needed the use of that oven.  So off I went to drop the pizza off at Eastons so that he could finish it off and decided I was going fishing.  Stressed and not wanting to be in the kitchen anymore.  And here is what I caught.    Now if I can only remember to bring along my ofncommunity.com sign I would be doing ok.  Hope everyone has a great weekend!  I look forward to all the posts... Off to Quinte in the morning with camera and SIGN in hand!  Cheers,  Jen
wow nice cat jen I've yet to get a catfish unbelievable because everybody fishin with me gets em.All I seem to get are walleye.
Good pic a cougar and a catfish
Nice on Jen, hope you do as well with the pickeral this weekend.
Nice Kitty ya got there Gal!!!  You can scribble OFNcommunity.com on anything with a lipstick or eyebrow liner pencil and it'll be legal.
Nice fat cat...
gee i aint even caught a cat that big !!lol    wtg jen!!!
Beauty catch Jen!! MMMM catfish on the barbacue.  Cheers, 1leg
Congrats Jen, nice cat.
Nice fish! Congrats Jen! I've caught one Catfish before, it was probably half of that, but was still a good experience, I caught it out of the Nith River. I love how Catfish strike so fast!
Nice size catfish jen. Least it better than the ones I caught with bkisters and bruises.    dsn
Nice fish! The OFC sign is still floating around in Simco somewhere.....LOL!  Glad to see you had a good time.  Easton

Not only was fishing for these guys fun it was a great fight.  A couple of them were caught on a big muskie rod and then a couple on a light rod with 6lb test... ( I learned it is all about setting the drag)  I hope to see a pickeral that big this weekend... YEAH RIGHT!! (secretly keeping my fingers crossed)  Thanks for the comments guys!  Cheers,  Jen
Those Guys are so lucky having someone cook for them I hope you catch the big for doing all the hard work.I will see you guys tonight.  Nice CAT Jen  MTP

Get on the road Mike LOL! See you later tonight, we are leaving here within the next hour and a half.....If Jen catches a walleye that big I am sure it will make her weekend. I am sure we will have an OFC sign or two floating around, (no pun intended Jen for loosing your old sign out the back of the boat and floating round Simcoe somewhere).  Easton
Nice fish! Now you can be a redneck!
nice catfish, good work!
congrats on the kittie wtg
Holy Catfish Batman!!!  Nice one Jen.  Joey
GREAT JOB!!good fish!!!  Mmmmm catfish.... now that you like em you gona try noodling for them? lol
Wow! NIce  size kitty!  And I have to say...looks   like a picture of beauty and the beast.
Agreed!!  Congrats on the fish!  Cheers!

Wow....great job and awesome looking fish!  Must have been lots of fun pulling that guy.  Your smile says it all.  Keep up the great work and dont worry about the OFC sign...you'll catch a bigger one anyways!!
wow - congrats Jen!
Great looking cat. Congrats and I hope opener goes well for you and the gang. I'll be watching for the report when you return.
